<subSubSection id="15DE5FE0FFA7EF64FF42F9CBFDFBF8BC" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFFA7EF64FF42F9CBFD7AF958" blockId="15.[151,1436,1589,1797]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFA7EF64FF42F9CBFEE7F920" bold="true" box="[199,338,1662,1688]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Comments:</emphasis>
This is the first record of the species since its original description, previously known only by the 
<typeStatus id="827FB2C9FFA7EF64FF12F917FF49F904" box="[151,252,1698,1724]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">holotype</typeStatus>
, and we were able to collect other 
<specimenCount id="4BC2C7E2FFA7EF64FDFFF917FD41F904" box="[634,756,1698,1724]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="male">four males</specimenCount>
. All individuals collected at ParNa Iguaçu were green, differing from the 
<typeStatus id="827FB2C9FFA7EF64FEACF973FE3EF958" box="[297,395,1734,1760]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">holotype</typeStatus>
that is light brown coloured.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFFA7EF64FF42F95FFDFBF8BC" blockId="15.[151,1436,1589,1797]" box="[199,590,1770,1797]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
